# Environment variables for the go aggregator web app (Next.js 15, App Router).
#
# Copy to `.env.local` for local development. In Next.js only variables prefixed
# with NEXT_PUBLIC_ are inlined into the browser bundle; every other variable is
# available only to server-side code (the API route handlers under app/api/*).
# Never commit real secrets — `.env.local` is git-ignored.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Client (browser) — NEXT_PUBLIC_*
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# URL prefix the app is served under. Leave BLANK for local `next dev` and for
# the Vercel deployment, where the app lives at the domain root. Set to `/go`
# ONLY for the GitHub Pages static export, where the site is served from the
# `/go` project-pages path. This mirrors the old Vite `import.meta.env.BASE_URL`
# and is what withBase() (web/src/basePath.ts) uses to prefix manual fetch()s
# for the bundled data files (graph.json, search-index.json, docs/*.json).
#
# The Pages build sets this on the command line — you normally do NOT set it here:
#   GITHUB_PAGES=true NEXT_PUBLIC_BASE_PATH=/go npm run build
NEXT_PUBLIC_BASE_PATH=

# NOTE: there is no client-side API URL variable. The search + package-graph API
# is served by Next route handlers (/api/graphql, /api/search, /api/health) on
# the SAME host as the app, so the frontend always calls it same-origin.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Server (API route handlers) — Elasticsearch, NOT committed
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# Elasticsearch is enabled server-side by these two variables. They are set in
# the Vercel project environment (Project Settings -> Environment Variables),
# NOT in this file and NOT in the client bundle. When they are unset the API
# routes transparently fall back to an in-memory BM25 ranker, and on hosts with
# no server functions (e.g. GitHub Pages) the frontend falls back to the bundled
# data files. Do not put these secrets in a committed `.env.example`/`.env.local`.
#
# ELASTICSEARCH_URL=https://<your-cluster>.es.cloud:443
# ELASTICSEARCH_API_KEY=<base64-encoded-api-key>
